.
I know I’m a few days late, but here’s my August reading wrap-up! Overall, I managed six books this month (including two eBooks not pictured here) and experienced both great and disappointing books. 
.
Children of Blood and Bone was definitely the highlight of my reading month; it was fast-paced, brilliantly written, and wholly unashamed to discuss themes such as genocide, racism, colourism and war with brutal honesty. It was an epic beginning to the series, and I’m very much looking forward to reading its sequel later this autumn. 
.
