I LOVE the 'word hoards' at the beginning of each chapter, under headings like Waterlands, Underlands and Edgelands. As MacFarlane says 'This is a book about the power of language - strong style, single words - to shape our sense of place.'

I had to keep a notebook by my side whilst reading it, to make note of all the things I wanted to find out more about and the books I wanted to read.

I've read a lot more nature writing since this but it still shines out brightly in my memory.

